Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.14,0:00:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What I wanted...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.54,0:00:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,has changed
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.47,0:00:28.47,Red,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1056,658)}Mahjong Midori
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.51,0:00:32.28,white-large,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1368,658)}Summer: Shōwa Year 33 (1958)
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.48,0:00:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The kind of change that would turn everything around.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.82,0:00:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,A rebirth.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.02,0:00:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,however
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.06,0:00:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I lack that quality.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.56,0:00:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My stock debts.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.98,0:00:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Losses at gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.98,0:01:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything I touched failed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.00,0:01:06.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And now this game of Mahjong I'm playing to erase my debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.74,0:01:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.34,0:01:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm caught. Finishing 3rd or 4th.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.85,0:01:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the game flow, my points are decreasing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.54,0:01:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And each time my my chest tightens.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.20,0:01:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've used it all up. Because of the large debts I had to sign a generous life insurance policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.37,0:01:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't deal into his hand again.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.97,0:02:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This time...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.17,0:02:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron. Riichi chitoitsu. Four thousand six hundred points.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.31,0:02:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax. I've got to do something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.22,0:03:00.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.45,0:04:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,My starting tiles are so bad I could cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.20,0:04:26.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But I haven't made any obvious mistakes. WHY?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.25,0:04:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,This north-south game.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.08,0:04:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm in last place it's over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't go onto the next game
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.08,0:04:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, at least place third...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.08,0:04:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, someone help me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.08,0:04:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Turn it around for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.08,0:04:45.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Reverse this stagnant air.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.50,0:04:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.37,0:04:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Even unto a demon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.94,0:05:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's that? There's someone there.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.68,0:05:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.88,0:05:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Find somewhere else to hide from the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.82,0:05:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Get the hell out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.82,0:05:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second. I invited him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.62,0:06:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.51,0:06:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If I didn't contact him by midnight, I told him to come looking for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.05,0:06:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.46,0:06:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.88,0:06:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.36,0:06:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you give him some coffee and a towel?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.65,0:06:57.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, all I wanted was a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.25,0:07:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sneaky bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.46,0:07:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Coffee for me too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.17,0:07:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Idiot!\NI'll have a water!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.57,0:07:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dampened. The heat of that game is fading.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.42,0:07:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The tide may be turning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.51,0:07:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You're soaked through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.97,0:07:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Let's get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.57,0:07:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no reason to think I'm through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.31,0:07:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't give up. Hang in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.34,0:08:05.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:20.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Discard the 5 Pin tile and it's a 1/4 Pin wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.80,0:08:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If I draw a 1 Pin, my one Dora tile raises the hand's value to Haneman.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.22,0:08:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,A hand that can put me on top, and turn the game around completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.03,0:08:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I really want to discard the 5 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.54,0:08:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's pretty dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.00,0:08:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,By the same token, the 2 Pin is a completely safe tile.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.02,0:08:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But I'll end up with a less valuable dragon hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.88,0:08:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I'll achieve Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.58,0:08:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.58,0:09:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,If I deal into his hand, it's over for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.39,0:09:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If I make Tenpai, I'm guaranteed 3rd place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, I have to do what I must.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.71,0:09:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a rough point.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.77,0:09:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You'd survive if only you {\b1}died{\b0}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.68,0:09:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know how to play Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.37,0:09:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Not at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.85,0:09:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But just now it looked like you died.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.68,0:09:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Your back doesn't have the strength to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.54,0:09:50.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're just afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.05,0:10:03.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.54,0:10:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But he's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.22,0:10:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How on earth could I discard the 2 Pin with this hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.22,0:10:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't know what I was thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.65,0:10:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,With this kind of thinking I'll never come out on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.57,0:10:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The man who never sets a single foot on a dangerous bridge
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.31,0:10:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,does he have any chance of winning at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.55,0:10:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm gambling for fuck's sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.17,0:10:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm going to die anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.97,0:10:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I might as well go out playing hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.42,0:11:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.51,0:11:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.85,0:11:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Red Dragon. Chanta SanSyoku. One Dora. Haneman.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.31,0:12:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Time for a short break.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.00,0:12:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.84,0:12:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid. How old are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.77,0:12:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirteen.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.65,0:12:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't look it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.25,0:12:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.11,0:12:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi Shigeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.97,0:14:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.94,0:14:13.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.40,0:14:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You're soaked through. But not by the rain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.02,0:14:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Your shirt smells of salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.94,0:14:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.94,0:14:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to talk about anything you don't want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.28,0:14:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe before you came here
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.28,0:14:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,you crossed that line between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.93,0:14:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:46.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now I'm walking that same line myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.17,0:14:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see it on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.48,0:15:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Tonight, if I don't win...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These bastards will kill me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.28,0:15:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Your back doesn't have the strength to win.\N You're just scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.82,0:15:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,For fuck's sake I'm gambling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.22,0:15:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.76,0:15:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.93,0:15:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. Do this for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.93,0:15:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Play the next north-south game in my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.07,0:16:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand that you don't know any Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.98,0:16:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I feel that that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.98,0:16:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,A guy with superficial knowledge may be easy prey...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.54,0:16:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But I feel from you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.74,0:16:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got what it takes to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.00,0:16:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Luck and craziness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.67,0:16:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the things I lack. Completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.97,0:16:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,With you, I just might be able to cross that line between life and death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.94,0:16:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then. Can we make a deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.11,0:16:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A deal?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.11,0:16:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.05,0:16:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,The legend would later rock the foundations of the Mahjong underworld...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.54,0:16:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi Shigeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.54,0:17:00.85,Default,,0,0,0,,would begin here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.85,0:17:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,His first time playing Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.47,0:17:08.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At this time, just five minutes before the game started.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.54,0:17:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,with only a simple explanation of the rules by Nangou
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.51,0:17:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and not knowing a single Yaku,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.51,0:17:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,he was less than a beginner.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.38,0:17:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But, during play,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.54,0:17:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi will little by little come to understand Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.93,0:17:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That a hand in Mahjong is made up of four Melds and one pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.86,0:17:32.76,purple,,0,0,0,,{\pos(844,140)}Melds
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.60,0:17:32.76,light-blue,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1618,126)}Pair
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.10,0:17:35.67,light-yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(912,190)}Yaku: San Syoku Doujyun Value: 2 Han (closed hand)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.77,0:17:38.77,light-yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(834,184)}Yaku: Ikkitsuukan Value: 2 Han (closed hand)
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.10,0:17:41.61,light-yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(620,184)}Yaku: Toitoihou Value: 2 Han
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.54,0:17:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it is a game where players compete on the speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.22,0:17:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and point values of their completed hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.67,0:17:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and that calling Pon and Chi
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.57,0:17:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,is best avoided whenever possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.80,0:17:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.12,0:17:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That white, green, and red dragon
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.45,0:17:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,are useful because a triplet of each is worth one Han.\NA convenient combination.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.39,0:17:57.76,light-yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(516,204)}Value: 1 Han
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.62,0:18:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That there is a special Yaku called Chiitoitsu that is made up of seven pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.59,0:18:04.36,light-yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(718,150)}Yaku: Chiitoitsu Value: 25 Fu 2 Han
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.45,0:18:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.\NChiitoitsu with two Dora tiles. Three Thousand/Six Thousand Points.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.09,0:18:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of the East round, Akagi had lost 7,200 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.08,0:18:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn't dealt into anyone's hand, nor has he won himself. An ordinary outcome.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.82,0:18:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it. A winning hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.97,0:19:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.05,0:19:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly a new player that doesn't call tiles is admirable
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.94,0:19:50.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but with that hand you've got to call Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.08,0:20:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,that hand will end up merely a Chiitoitsu!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.54,0:20:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over. He has no sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.82,0:20:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Trusting this kid with everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.14,0:20:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have been nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.61,0:20:34.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me for disturbing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.61,0:20:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's a police officer here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.61,0:20:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,There's been an incident. Would you let us in?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.11,0:20:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pain in the ass.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.11,0:20:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,hold on there!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.34,0:20:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ryuzaki. Still mediocre at Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.80,0:20:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well Detective, what can I do for you this evening?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.94,0:21:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, really, last night there was a car accident involving rival gangs.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.14,0:21:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We have information one suspect fled to this vicinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.02,0:21:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Some punk's fight has nothing to do with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.34,0:21:25.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki. Recently in this neighborhood smuggled handguns have been circulating.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.25,0:21:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what about?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.77,0:21:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're inclined, may we search the premises?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.88,0:21:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.91,0:21:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut that shit out.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.22,0:21:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Nangou-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.97,0:21:42.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what I'm bargaining with.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.48,0:21:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Bargain?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.48,0:21:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. If the police come looking for me
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.28,0:21:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Our stories must match, and you vouch for my alibi and identity.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.30,0:22:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't bargain if you have nothing to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.40,0:22:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have something soon enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.77,0:22:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,A DaiSanGen SuuAnKou.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.45,0:22:15.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.45,0:22:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier surely it looked like...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.29,0:22:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The little bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.26,0:22:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He swapped tiles from the discards.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.90,0:22:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what a 'Chicken Run' is , don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.87,0:22:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Two cars racing towards a cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.05,0:22:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoever brakes first, loses. Seems like fun, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.71,0:22:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Last night they failed, stupidly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.60,0:22:58.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end both the bastards went off the cliff.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.37,0:23:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One was seriously hurt.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.37,0:23:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,One fell into the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.37,0:23:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And he swam off on his own.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.20,0:23:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you. The one that survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.54,0:23:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,No. It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.80,0:23:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.21,0:23:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my nephew.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.85,0:23:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He's been here since 6 last night.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.54,0:23:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this true, Ryuzaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.20,0:23:43.20,Default,,0,0,0,,This is bad. Because I protected this guy
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.20,0:23:46.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Will they give me away?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.02,0:23:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's so, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.97,0:23:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.45,0:24:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ahh. Yeah. He's been here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.25,0:24:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow he's made buddies with the Yakuza.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.57,0:24:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got an eye witness.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.97,0:24:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, there are footprints left on the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.45,0:24:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,If the guy escaped he'd leave soaking wet footprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.69,0:24:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are from earlier when I went out to buy cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.22,0:24:44.94,Default,,0,0,0,,In this rain?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:44.94,0:24:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But as I thought, the shop was closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.97,0:24:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him I couldn't go at this hour, but he wouldn't take no for an answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.05,0:24:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Pops.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.71,0:25:05.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He was also pretty irritated because he'd been losing a lot. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.52,0:25:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And I don't know what a 'chicken run' is in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.48,0:25:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Would someone who would do that be relaxing and playing Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.13,0:25:23.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if he played in place of someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.13,0:25:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would the people here protect him?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.60,0:25:31.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing for them to gain by that.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.18,0:25:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So, shall we begin?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.52,0:25:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well done!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.52,0:25:52.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He made them resume the game while everyone's attention was on the cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.63,0:25:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore they haven't yet noticed the tiles he's switched.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.91,0:26:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now, they might just discard the tile he needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.34,0:26:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.99,0:26:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,A DaiSanGen SuAnkou!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.99,0:26:25.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You little...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.99,0:26:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,??????????
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.71,0:26:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.71,0:26:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning with such an especially strong hand for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.25,0:26:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,normally, this cheat no one saw...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.22,0:26:49.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the Yakuza wouldn't stand for it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.22,0:26:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,They would inevitably resort to violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.46,0:26:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,To prevent that from happening
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.97,0:26:59.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He lured the cops here from the start to be witnesses.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.25,0:27:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a bitch.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.44,0:27:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Make damn sure this is the last time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.14,0:27:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Pull another trick around us
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.25,0:27:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We take this
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.95,0:27:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Break time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.00,0:27:48.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That kid's creepy, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.41,0:27:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he got here they've won twice in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.42,0:27:57.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we contact Yagi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.88,0:27:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Do it
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.22,0:28:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.22,0:28:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean our rep player
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.14,0:28:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.17,0:28:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you delirious?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.77,0:28:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.31,0:28:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,All he did was cheat his way into a DaiSanGen SuuAnkou
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.05,0:28:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,He's an amateur. The proof is that he discards dangerous tiles with ease.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.31,0:28:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's sheer chance he hasn't played into anyone's hand yet
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.76,0:28:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,y-yessir
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.76,0:28:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, we three go all out at him.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.91,0:28:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,His beginner's luck is about to run out
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.02,0:28:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah. The rainstorm hasn't stopped  yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.97,0:29:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No it hasn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.22,0:29:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I might stay here out of the rain for a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.45,0:29:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You head back
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.74,0:29:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.74,0:29:09.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yasuoka-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.65,0:29:15.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if this bastard's the real thing or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.05,0:29:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Look at this. This is an iipeikou
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.31,0:29:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It's worth one Han
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.31,0:29:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Be careful, it's no good if you call tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.61,0:29:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a SanShoku
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.94,0:29:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's worth two Han
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.57,0:29:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Worth one Han if you call tiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.00,0:29:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.00,0:29:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is called a Honitsu
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.02,0:29:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's made of honors and tiles of the same suit
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.28,0:29:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Hold on there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.57,0:29:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know how to play Mahjong?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.62,0:29:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,No. That was my first time just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.37,0:29:54.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Honitsu is worth three Han
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.34,0:29:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If you call tiles, it's worth two Han.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.05,0:30:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You. Literally playing against Yakuza.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.92,0:30:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What in the world are you thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.28,0:30:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.02,0:30:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That was tricky.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.51,0:30:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Calmly discarding that tile against that riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.74,0:30:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not a tile to discard with a chance of Ippatsu
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.65,0:30:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A pure amateur move
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.14,0:31:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Again with the 4 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.74,0:31:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,One glance and you can see he should discard that 3 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.05,0:31:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Having 2 Man 3 Man 3 Man 4 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.79,0:31:23.93,yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(528,274)}SyanPon\N(Wait with two pairs to make 3 of a kind)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.79,0:31:23.93,yellow,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1370,72)}Ryanmen (double sided wait)
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.51,0:31:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(912,946)}There are five possible winning waits after declaring Tenpai
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.45,0:31:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Better by far.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.45,0:31:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, having 4 Pin, 4 Pin, 5 Pin and 6 Pin
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.80,0:31:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There are about five waits, including bad middle waits.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.71,0:31:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a shanpon wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.71,0:31:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,His decisions at this point have been quick, and correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.68,0:31:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not the thinking of someone who started playing for the first time just a few hours ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.31,0:31:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.11,0:32:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I just don't get it
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.75,0:32:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lucky that tile passed so effortlessly.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.02,0:32:30.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the luck he was born with?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.65,0:32:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,With this hand you'd probably want to discard the 5 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.60,0:32:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But that's unwise because from the discards it's clear it's an Ura Suji.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.22,0:32:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And what's more it's a Dora.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.85,0:32:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And with a wall of 3 Man tiles
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.00,0:33:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps discard the 2 Man?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.33,0:33:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey. Just wait a second now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.33,0:33:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,t-that's crazy!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.94,0:33:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this little tile so dangerous?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.54,0:33:12.54,Default,,0,0,0,,y-yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.54,0:33:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a likely winner. It's a glaringly obvious Ura Suji
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.94,0:33:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So for example, let's say you have a 4 Sou and a 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.71,0:33:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you draw a 3 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.71,0:33:27.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It becomes a 3 Sou 4 Sou 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.22,0:33:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You discard the 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.22,0:33:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore the discarded 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.42,0:33:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Indicates a common double wait pattern
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.51,0:33:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And furthermore, that tile...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.77,0:33:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,OI NANGOU
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.77,0:33:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just relax m8
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.77,0:33:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You promised to just teach the Yaku.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.68,0:33:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.60,0:33:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nangou-san
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.60,0:33:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a Dora isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.85,0:33:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,b-but you know that!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.22,0:33:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,But that doesn't matter at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.45,0:34:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,See? It passed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.82,0:34:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's only hindsight! If you keep playing like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:23.20,0:34:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Cut it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.20,0:34:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mentanpin
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.00,0:34:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,3 thousand 9 hundred points
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.32,0:34:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.51,0:34:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,South round 2 first game. Akagi gradually closes in points.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.31,0:34:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming first in this half game as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.51,0:34:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsumo.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.51,0:35:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The Akagi-Nangou team wins three games in a row.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.20,0:35:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.02,0:35:13.97,Default,,0,0,0,,As we thought, this can't go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.00,0:35:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,"His beginner's luck ends here"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.45,0:35:19.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Right breh?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.45,0:35:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Quit joking around!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.91,0:35:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,HOW!?!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.34,0:35:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I allowed that Yakuman he cheated his way into.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.20,0:35:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But this half game is different.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.85,0:35:33.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It's losing to a stronger opponent.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.71,0:35:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Losing to someone who's played Mahjong for only a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.25,0:35:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll look like idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.97,0:35:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Bro
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.31,0:35:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to prevent him from coming top in these last two rounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.62,0:35:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If that happens' we'll have to shoulder Nangou's debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.77,0:36:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Call Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.62,0:36:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.62,0:36:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to make sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.00,0:36:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,yessir
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.34,0:36:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That Ryuzaki guy
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.14,0:36:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He makes his living beating novices at Mahjong.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.08,0:36:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard he's not a bad player.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.77,0:36:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And you're driving him nuts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.02,0:36:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a ridiculous misstatement.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.76,0:36:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He bets large sums of money
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.22,0:36:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to take it off novices and big talkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.48,0:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But in a high pressure situation, with a strong opponent
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.00,0:37:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,His bare Mahjong skill is that of a child.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.34,0:37:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.34,0:37:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But you're the same, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.51,0:37:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, you've only played Mahjong for a few hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.34,0:37:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Except you didn't deal into his hand once.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.14,0:37:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask you...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.77,0:37:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,just what are you seeing?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.26,0:37:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Detective
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.26,0:37:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you had this hand, for example, what tile would you discard?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.05,0:37:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case, the 8 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.65,0:37:57.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.97,0:38:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The 7 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.77,0:38:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The 7 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.02,0:38:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Detective, can you see the difference between discarding the 8 Man and the 7 Pin?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.11,0:38:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the... difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.14,0:38:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At first glance, it looks like the 8 Man and 7 Pin were discarded similarly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:23.82,0:38:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But they enter the discards pile...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.60,0:38:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,they impart entirely different information.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.14,0:38:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The 8 Man in this hand
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.40,0:38:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not related to any possible melds.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.40,0:38:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus there are no waits around the discarded 8 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.20,0:38:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand if we discard the 7 Pin from this hand...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.37,0:38:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,There are tiles consecutive to it,\Nso therefore there are waits around the 7 Pin.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.31,0:38:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Tiles around the discarded 8 Man are safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.62,0:38:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But tiles around the 7 Pin are dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.42,0:39:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Discarded tiles in Mahjong can for the most part be divided into these two categories.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.74,0:39:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You could say, the Safe Zone, and the Danger Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.59,0:39:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course there are tiles that don't fit into either category.\Nand which aren't more than noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.37,0:39:15.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Every discarded tile can therefore be 100% explained.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.47,0:39:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's think about a more concrete case from reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.71,0:39:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you remember these discards?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.51,0:39:42.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, yeah. Those are absolutely Ryuzaki's\Nwhen you discarded the 5 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.20,0:39:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.11,0:39:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That time Nangou tried to stop me
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.28,0:39:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just w-wait a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.77,0:39:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a likely winner.\NA galringly obvious Ura Suji.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.25,0:39:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had absolute certainty it would pass.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.05,0:40:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,H-how?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.48,0:40:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He discarded the 6 Sou too early.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.48,0:40:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,This means that to Ryuzaki the value of the 6 Sou...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.42,0:40:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,was lower than that of the 8 Man or 9 Pin discarded later.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.02,0:40:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And similarly,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.02,0:40:20.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It meant there were no tiles next to the 6 Sou in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.05,0:40:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If there had been a 4 Sou near the 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.22,0:40:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or an 8 Sou, he wouldn't have discarded the 6 Sou to begin with.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.68,0:40:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He might have had...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.17,0:40:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,A 2 Sou or 3 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.17,0:40:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but when he discarded his 1 Sou draw on the 8th turn,\Neven that possibility disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.08,0:40:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,He had no Sou tiles left.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.08,0:40:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,From the early discard of the 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.80,0:40:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It was basically clear he had no more Sou tiles in his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.11,0:40:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The area around the 6 Sou is a Safe Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.51,0:40:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the Safe Zone?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.08,0:40:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And in reverse, the truly Dangerous Zone in these discards
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.28,0:41:01.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Is the 1 Man he clung to until the 6th turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.05,0:41:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1 Man was more important than the 6 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.17,0:41:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it meant he had a tile near his 1 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.17,0:41:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I had basically decided he had a 1 Man and a 3 Man
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.60,0:41:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you also consider this 4 Man discarded right after...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.94,0:41:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The 1 Man and the 4 Man were likely from this arrangement.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.85,0:41:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Made it pretty obvious he was waiting for a 2 or 5 Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.88,0:41:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A classic example of a Danger Zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.82,0:41:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way it was possible to classify Ryuzaki's discards like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.17,0:41:37.78,light-blue,,0,0,0,,{\pos(660,132)}Safe Zone
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.94,0:41:37.78,Red,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1230,128)}Danger Zone
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.37,0:41:37.78,light green,,0,0,0,,{\pos(1026,930)}Noise
Dialogue: 0,0:41:31.31,0:41:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And his last 4 Pin which doesn't fit in either category, I regard as noise.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.58,0:41:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.58,0:41:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But there's something odd
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.14,0:41:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely the 4 Pin he discarded right after declaring riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.09,0:41:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Even Supposing he wanted a 1 or 5 Man tile
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.37,0:41:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't discard your 6 Pin for fear of Ippastu.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.42,0:41:59.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was it still in the Safe Zone?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.97,0:42:06.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In reading a match, you have more than the discards.\NThere are other approaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.97,0:42:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,During the game Ryuzaki had this hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.88,0:42:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.74,0:42:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,There wasn't as single Sou tile in his hand, just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.74,0:42:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew he had a tile right beneath his 4 Sou
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.25,0:42:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and his Pin melds were complete
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.48,0:42:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And what remained for him to wait on?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.48,0:42:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.48,0:42:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Surely you can't know that.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.00,0:42:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,However
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.00,0:42:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki has a bit of a habit.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.02,0:42:40.77,Default,,0,0,0,,"Habit?"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.77,0:42:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after that riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.22,0:42:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He glanced left.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.42,0:42:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. In so many words.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.42,0:42:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He was looking at his Man tiles to confirm he was in Tenpai.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.94,0:43:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment the chance of him waiting on Pin tiles was gone.\NHe was only waiting on Man tiles, namely a 2 or a 5.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.23,0:43:08.23,Default,,0,0,0,,A 2-5 Wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.23,0:43:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,This bastard.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.23,0:43:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In his first hours playing Mahjong
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.17,0:43:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The essence of the discards laid bare before him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.82,0:43:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And that last insight.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.25,0:43:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Already Ryuzaki is no match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.94,0:43:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He's already surpassed him by far.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.94,0:43:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,From here that Yakuza will be torn to bits.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.60,0:43:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The talent of a genius has awakened in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.33,0:43:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Akagi Shigeru
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.33,0:43:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,That limitless talent
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.42,0:43:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Had been awakened.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.60,0:44:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming top in two more rounds and I'm free!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.17,0:44:08.37,Default,,0,0,0,,My 3 million yen debt... erased!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.37,0:44:11.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm counting on you, Akagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.57,0:44:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay on this wave and finish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.70,0:44:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.57,0:44:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.60,0:44:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Riichi Ippatsu Tanyao one Dora
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.40,0:44:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A Mangan!?!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.31,0:45:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,After the East round, Akagi leads, with Ryuzaki in 2nd, 22,000 points behind.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.57,0:45:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You little bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.90,0:45:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yagi san?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.20,0:45:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.04,0:45:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at last the Pro appears, hunh?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.82,0:45:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Even a cop here.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.05,0:45:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You babysitting tonight?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.40,0:45:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki, having a hard time?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.48,0:45:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You took someone way too lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.96,0:45:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Please don't take his debts so lightly.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.40,0:45:55.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll play as expected?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.42,0:45:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I've seen the kid's hand
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.94,0:45:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to sit this round out.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:59.94,0:46:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's still the whole South round left isn't there?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.20,0:46:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,The next round's more than enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.45,0:46:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.60,0:46:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,He's lucky.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.62,0:46:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Since he's in the lead,  that's an express ticket to victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.80,0:46:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The red dragon pair is just what he needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.88,0:47:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,W-What the--!?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.65,0:47:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,He suddenly discarded his red dragon pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.74,0:48:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Fucking brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.31,0:48:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If he didn't discard that red dragon pair.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.14,0:48:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't have thought to discard mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.51,0:48:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.88,0:48:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,If he hadn't discarded that red dragon pair, maybe a ShoSan--
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.28,0:48:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.57,0:48:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If Akagi had discarded those dragons just a bit later,\NRyuzaki would have gotten a DaiSanGen.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.51,0:49:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point he's leaving humanity behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.02,0:49:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,He smelled the DaiSanGen from just the white dragon being called.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.45,0:49:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,He foresaw the danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.00,0:49:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,His sensitivity is three turns quicker than a normal person.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.05,0:49:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's two tiles from a SanSyoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.02,0:49:40.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Pon.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.82,0:49:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Chi.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.62,0:50:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,He throws away the SanShoku without remorse.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.88,0:50:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and he's in Tenpai?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.77,0:50:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.36,0:50:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Tanyao. 1000 points.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.60,0:50:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,A normal player would be hesitant to drop that SanShoku.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.74,0:50:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he knew Ryuzaki could win at any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.02,0:50:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,However
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.02,0:50:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the kid knows how much hesitation would slow him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.82,0:50:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ryuzaki is simply no match for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:40.00,0:50:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond question.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.96,0:50:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The only concern now is this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.16,0:50:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi Keiji.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.54,0:50:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.13,0:50:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,We need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:23.20,0:51:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yagi-san. Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.80,0:53:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,One finger for 100,000 Yen.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.40,0:53:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, if when it's time to settle accounts
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.80,0:53:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,you pay the same price.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.57,0:53:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, I accept.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.57,0:53:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll teach you
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.57,0:53:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the Achilles' Heel of riichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.28,0:53:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Someone whose thoughts only deal with cheating others.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.31,0:53:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Superficial thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.65,0:53:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Kan!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.22,0:53:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's come!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.42,0:53:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You're such an idiot, Yagi-san.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.42,0:53:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all I can take. Please stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.20,0:53:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He can't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.68,0:53:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.65,0:53:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ron.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.57,0:53:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it's not over yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.25,0:54:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's double-or-nothing!
